6241378301.text: @rhysiedarby Thanks for your astro thoughts Rhys... worked a charm.

6241333403.text: Rocket Lab technical team still on Great Mercury Island looking to recover the 2nd stage payload section of Manu Karere.

6216073845.text: 1st stage booster recovered today, recovery confirmed that the engine burn was excellent. Still looking for 2nd stage payload section.

6192586178.text: If found please mark the payload location, and relay the GPS coordinates to Rocket Lab ASAP.

6192102159.text: Awaiting GPS coordinates over the Iridium network. The payload section is expected to be around 50 kilometres NE of Great Mercury Island.

6191965660.text: A successful launch! Lift off at 2.28pm and an exemplary 22 second burn. The team are ecstatic! NZ, thank you for all your support!

6123890044.text: Monday weather forecasts looking good for the launch at 7.10am. Will likely be covered live on TV1 and TV3 in New Zealand.

6105062758.text: Auckland to Whitianga this morning, then crew, gear and rocket landed on Great Mercury Island. Now it's time to setup the launch site..

6044617471.text: Payload integration now complete and tonight finishing off installation of launch rail cameras.

6041210266.text: Tonight Manu Karere is being readied for transport. Will depart for Great Mercury Island early Friday morning.

6041133794.text: Local iwi Ngati Hei named the first rocket 'Manu Karere', translates as 'Bird Messenger'. Ātea-1 is the name of the first rocket series.

6002312499.text: New launch time likely to be 7.10am on Mon and live coverage on TV3

5863404901.text: Ātea-1 counting down to launch on November 30th, 6.30am.
